sentences.english: Like those tadpoles, we grew legs and hopped off into the world.
sentences.chinese: 像那些蝌蚪一样，我们也逐渐成长，并跃进了世界。

sentences.english: Both fish and tadpoles have gills.
Little Tadpoles Looking for their Mommy is one of the stories We are familiar with.
sentences.chinese: 小蝌蚪找妈妈就是我们其中最熟悉的一个故事。

sentences.english: A tadpole metamorphoses into a frog.
Trout feed on tadpoles and young frogs.
sentences.chinese: 鲑鱼捕食蝌蚪和小青蛙。

sentences.english: Firstly I took the stones in a circle, leave an entrance to tadpoles.
sentences.chinese: 我先把石头筑成了一个坝，只给小蝌蚪留一个入口。

sentences.english: If a frog is changed from a tadpole, I won't play with a frog.
sentences.chinese: 如果青蛙是由蝌蚪变来的，那我不愿意和一只青蛙玩。

sentences.english: The tadpole produce the sound by pushing air out of their lungs.
sentences.chinese: 这种蝌蚪通过将空气从肺中挤出，来发出声音。

sentences.english: Shall those tadpoles had ears, they must have heard their fellows' calls.
sentences.chinese: 这些蝌蚪倘有耳，一定也会听见它们的同类的歌声。

sentences.english: Joint-toxicity of copper and hydrargyrum on tadpole was studied in the present investigation.
sentences.chinese: 研究了铜和汞共存对泽蛙蝌蚪的联合毒性。

sentences.english: At the corner, some little tadpoles are sleeping.
sentences.chinese: 在角落里，小蝌蚪们睡着了。

sentences.english: The tadpoles metamorphose and emerge onto land.
Semen is a fluid in which sperms swim.
sentences.chinese: 牛奶是液体，蝌蚪游泳其中。

sentences.english: Tadpoles can be found in this rivulet.
sentences.chinese: 这条小溪里能见到蝌蚪。

sentences.english: Tadpole swimming in the water, very happy.
sentences.chinese: 小蝌蚪在水里游来游去，非常快乐。

definition: the young (unborn or newborn) of an animal/larva
